===Noun===
'''punk''' (''[[uncountable]] and [[countable]]''; ''plural'' '''punks''')

#(''uncountable'') Wood so decayed as to be dry, crumbly, and useful for tinder; touchwood.
#(''uncountable'') A fungus (''Polyporus fomentarius'', etc.) sometimes dried for tinder; agaric.
#(''uncountable'') An artificial tinder. See [[amadou]] and [[spunk]].
#(''countable'') A [[prostitute]]; a [[strumpet]].
#(''countable'') A person who is unwillingly [[sodomize]]d in prison.
#(''countable'') A homosexual male who is [[penetrate]]d during [[anal sex]].
#(''uncountable''; ''current in western society from the mid 1970s'') A social and musical movement that, originally, primarily involved rebelling against the established order such as wearing torn clothes, embracing discordance, and anarchy, and later mainstreamed as a fashion or style.
#(''countable'') A worthless person.

